Rowan Cos Inc said it expects to incursubstantial losses in 1987 despite expected improvement indrilling levels in the Gulf of Mexico and the North Sea.    The offshore and onshore drilling company today reported afirst quarter loss of 18.6 mln dlrs after a 12.2 mln dlr taxcredit, compared with a year-earlier loss of 5,855,000 dlrsafter a tax credit of 8,510,000 dlrs.  For all of 1986, Rowanlost 42.1 mln dlrs after a 47.6 mln dlr tax credit. Reuter&#3;